title: Tesla shares rise more than 7% after delivery and production numbers beat expectations
description: Tesla shares rose more than 7% in Monday morning trading, driven in part by stronger-than-expected second-quarter deliveries and production numbers.

title: Bluesky experiences 'record-high traffic' after Elon Musk imposes rate limits on Twitter
description: Bluesky said it experienced "record-high traffic" after Elon Musk said Twitter will temporarily limit the number of posts users can read per day.

title: Scotland's iconic Orkney Islands considering quitting Britain to become part of Norway
description: Scotland's iconic Orkney Islands archipelago is looking at ways it might split off from the U.K. and potentially become a self-governing territory of Norway.

title: Shares of Chinese Tesla rival Xpeng rocket 11% as EV deliveries return to growth
description: Xpeng said it delivered 23,205 cars in the second quarter of 2023, a 27% quarter-on-quarter rise, beating its own forecasts.

title: WWE legend pitches to hold Wrestlemania in UK as rival AEW gears up for major London show
description: WWE legend John Cena surprised fans at the Money in the Bank in the U.K. live event with a pitch to hold Wrestlemania in London for the first time.

title: EU and Japan look to partner on A.I. and chips as China 'de-risking' strategy continues
description: The EU is looking to "de-risk" from China, and part of that strategy involves deepening the relationship with allied countries around technology.

title: Japan launches Prime 150 stocks benchmark to help investors identify value
description: The new JPX Prime 150 Index, which launched Monday, is a curated list of 150 biggest Tokyo listings including the likes of Sony Group, Hitachi, Nintendo.

title: Wind turbine troubles have sent one stock tumbling. There are fears it could be a much wider issue
description: "We have to acknowledge that ... the pace of change in that machinery has put us into slightly uncharted territory," one analyst said.

title: Singapore names Deputy Prime Minister Lawrence Wong as chairman of the central bank
description: The Monetary Authority of Singapore named Deputy Prime Minister Lawrence Wong as Chairman of its Board of Directors effective July 8.

title: India's HDFC Bank completes $40 billion takeover of the country's largest mortgage lender. Here’s what it means
description: The HDFC-HDFC Bank merger took effect on July 1, following shareholder and regulatory approvals.

title: China's central bank gets a new party secretary
description: In China, the party secretary of an institution typically holds the most sway.

title: China's factory activity grew more slowly in June, Caixin survey shows
description: Official data last week pointed to stuttering growth in the world's second-largest economy.

title: Is India the next China? Analyst says he is 'very, very bullish' on one of them
description: India is not the new China, but the emerging superpower could "enjoy some very high growth years," said Riedel Research Group.

title: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen to meet with senior officials in China this week
description: Yellen's trip comes just weeks after Secretary of State Antony Blinken met with China's President Xi Jinping in Beijing.
